-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Tue Jun 03, 2014 06:13AM EDT
-- None



June 3 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1000 GMT on Tuesday:

** SoftBank Corp <9984.T> CEO Masayoshi Son said company officials are in regular contact with U.S. regulators although he has not met with them recently himself, as his company faces stiff regulatory resistance to a possible bid for U.S. wireless operator T-Mobile US Inc <TMUS.N>. [ID:nT9N0NT012]  ** Minority shareholders of Hong Kong-listed CITIC Pacific Ltd <0267.HK> are gathering to vote on a landmark deal to acquire $36 billion of assets from its state-owned parent CITIC Group Corp, China's biggest and oldest financial conglomerate. [ID:nL3N0OF2WY]  ** The main owner and chief executive of Russia's Severstal' OAO <CHMF.MM> said the sale of its U.S. business would be "an interesting option" that would allow the steelmaker to reduce its debt. [ID:nL6N0OK12K]  ** Pilgrim's Pride Corp <PPC.O> is planning to raise its offer for Hillshire Brands Co <HSH.N> a week after it first offered to buy the maker of Jimmy Dean Sausages in a $6.4 billion deal, the Wall Street Journal reported on Monday, citing people familiar with the matter. The new offer would value the meat company at $55 a share, according to one person, or more than $6.7 billion, the newspaper reported. [ID:nL1N0OK01X]  ** Swiss fragrance and flavor maker Givaudan SA <GIVN.VX> said it bought French cosmetic ingredients firm Soliance - its first acquisition since the $2.25 billion purchase of Quest International in March 2007. Givaudan did not disclose the price or other deal terms or the identity of the sellers of the privately owned firm. [ID:nL6N0OK0MK]  ** Element Financial Corp <EFN.TO> has agreed to buy PHH Corp's <PHH.N> auto fleet leasing business for about $1.4 billion in cash, and will issue $1.1 billion in capital to pay for the deal, the two companies said on Monday. [ID:nL1N0OJ0T1]  ** China Everbright International Ltd <0257.HK> has agreed to a reverse takeover of Singapore-listed HanKore Environment Tech Group <HETG.SI>, in which it will transfer its water treatment assets to HanKore for S$1.2 billion ($955.22 million) in shares. After the deal, China Everbright will hold 78 percent Hankore shares, and will rename the Singapore water treatment firm China Everbright Water Ltd, Hankore said in a statement late on Monday. [ID:nL3N0OK0CA]  ** Retailers Carrefour SA <CARR.PA> and Casino Guichard Perrachon SA <CASP.PA> made non-binding offers last week to buy DIA France, the loss-making French division that Spanish discount supermarket chain DIA SA <DIDA.MC> has put up for sale, Le Figaro daily said on Tuesday. Spanish bank Sabadell last month valued Dia French at around 500 million euros ($696.1 million) including debt. [ID:nL6N0OK0GX]  ** YuuZoo, a Singapore e-commerce firm run by the former Asia head of Finnish technology company Nokia Oyj <NOK1V.HE>, plans to go public through a S$490.9 million ($391 million) reverse takeover of W Corp Ltd <WCOR.SI>. [ID:nL3N0OK0FC]  ** Spanish infrastructure company Abertis Infraestructuras SA <ABE.MC> completed its exit from French satellite operator Eutelsat Communications SA <ETL.PA> on Tuesday by selling its remaining 5.01 percent stake in the company for 275 million euros ($374.2 million). [ID:nL6N0OK11I]